<HEADLINE> Workshop on Policy Analysis Opens in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A five-day workshop on policy
analysis and strategic management of public sector reforms
started here today with a call for governments to understand
problems in their context before formulating policies.
</P>
<P>
The workshop seeks to identify ways of improving coordination
between the ministries of finance and public service in policy
formulation and implementation, enable participants to understand
their situations in the context of regional and global trends and
improve policy formulation and management in a rapidly changing
global environment.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 participants drawn from the Southern African
Development Community region are attending the workshop.
</P>
<P>
Presenting a paper at the workshop, South Africa's Northwest
Province Director General of Administration Job Mokgoro said
there is need for public sector managers to decide which
dimensions of the problem are most important when developing
policies.
</P>
<P>
He said many developing countries continue to face economic
problems while their challenges are compounded by every
diminishing resources which make it difficult for state
departments to implement policy reforms.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, ''there is deterioration of prioritization of
development programs and projects yet implementing policy reforms
requires a comprehensive approach and not quick fixes.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
