<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Environment Chief to Meet ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Environment
Minister Yeo Cheow Tong will attend the 7th ASEAN (Association of
Southeast Asian Nations) Ministerial Meeting on the Environment in
Jakarta, Indonesia on Tuesday, the Ministry of the Environment
said today.
</P>
<P>
It is believed here that the worsening haze pollution problem
will top the agenda of the meeting to be hosted by Indonesia's
State Minister of Environment Sarwono Kusumaatmadja.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Ministry of Environment said the meeting,
held once every three years, would also discuss international
environment conventions and long-term environmental quality goals
for the ASEAN, which now groups Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand,
Singapore, the Philippines, Brunei, Vietnam, Myanmar and Laos.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will discuss environmental issues of common
interest and concern to the region, which will include
transboundary haze pollution, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
In Singapore, haze caused by forest fires and land cleaning
fires in Indonesia has worsened in the past two days while
Malaysia has declared the heavy haze, which has reached very
unhealthy level in the country, a national disaster.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
