<HEADLINE> Swedish Prime Minister to Brussels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 15 (Xinhua)-- Swedish Prime Minister
Goeran Persson will visit Brussels on September 22, according to
local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
He will have separate meetings with President of the EU
Commission Jacques Santer and NATO Secretary General Javier Solana.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with the NATO Secretary General, Swedish Prime
Minister Persson is expected to emphasize the importance of
bringing concrete contents into the Euro-Atlantic Partnership
Council, of which Sweden is a member. 
</P>
