<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern African Water Conference Opens in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Second Southern African
Conference on Water Environment started here today with a theme
of "Water Security: Guarding Resources Against Pollution and
Drought".
</P>
<P>
The five-day conference will underscore the need to utilize
and manage water resources in a sustainable manner.
</P>
<P>
The conference, sponsored by the British government, embodies
the 5th Exhibition of Water and Environmental Protection.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 companies and institutions are represented at
the conference with more than 50 coming from Europe, the United
States and the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
High on the agenda are river basin management, water
conversation, ground water, water economics, demand and pollution
control and private sector participation.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's Minister of Rural Resources and Water Development
Jyce Mururu said at the opening ceremony that the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) still has a lot to do in
terms of infrastructure development and management of scarce
water resources for sustainable development to be achieved in the
region.
</P>
<P>
She said the conference was being held against the background
of the lack of development, scarce water resources and growing
population pressures in the rural areas, which has raised the
demand for water especially in the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
"The scarcity of water has created economic, political,
social, technical and managerial problems," the minister
stressed.
</P>
<P>
According to Mururu, traumatic droughts in the region raised
the need for regional leaders to put water issues in the
forefront as they have impact on almost very aspect of
development.
</P>
<P>
The signing of the SADC protocol on shared water course
systems, she said, would greatly enhance collaborations between
countries in the region on matters of water utilization and
management.
</P>
<P>
The protocol signed in 1995 is expected to become operational
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
