<HEADLINE> Teenagers Mowed Down at Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- One teenager was killed and
two others seriously injured when a driver mowed down at least 15
teens at an outdoor party in the Canadian province of British
Columbia, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old high school student died at the scene. One of the
the severely injured teens has head and spinal injuries and might
be paralyzed. The other was in danger of losing a limb.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened Saturday at a teen party spot in Surrey,
a suburb of Vancouver. Some 200 teens were at the outdoor
back-to-school party.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that a youth driving a car plowed into the
crowd when he found his car blocked in by others.
</P>
<P>
"There were bodies everywhere," one witness was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
"Some were hit so hard they were knocked right out of their
shoes."
</P>
<P>
The youth, now arrested and in custody, faces charges including
impaired driving and criminal negligence causing death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
