<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Beats U.S. Teams in World Cup Preliminary Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Cuba scored victories in
both men's and women's matches over the United States on Sunday in
the preliminary round of the North and Central American and
Caribbean Volleyball Championships in Caguas of Puerto Rico.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban men defeated the United States 15-6, 15-10, 15-11 on
Sunday to remain unbeaten in three outings so far. The Cuban squad
are expected to meet the 2-1 United States in Friday's finals. The
winner qualifies for World Cup tournament in November in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Americans next plays Puerto Rico (1-2) on Tuesday. Mexico
(2-1) faces Barbados (1-2) in Tuesday's other match. Canada (3-0)
earned a bye by defeating Guatemala 15-3, 15-7, 15-0 Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban women's team, current world and Olympics champions,
also blocked their American rivals 3-0 on Sunday. Both team are
expected to play again for the gold on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. women were 2-1 and will meet Puerto Rico (1-2) on
Tuesday while Canada (2-1) plays Mexico (1-2). The Dominican
Republic (3-0) earned a bye by defeating Puerto Rico 15-4, 15-9,
15-5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
