<HEADLINE> European Shares up on Strong Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Leading stock markets in
Europe all made solid gains and ended strongly today, boosted by
Wall Street's surge Friday and its strong opening on Monday.
</P>
<P>
British shares on the London market ended 54.7 points or 1.13
percent higher at 4,902.9, strengthened by a strong performance on
Wall Street and gilts.
</P>
<P>
However, trading volumes were thin as some investors were
sidelined ahead of economic pointers due out this week. Meanwhile,
market sentiment was dominated by doubts over how robust Wall
Street's rise was.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index of German shares on the Frankfurt market,
which ends before Wall Street opens, ended 34.68 points weaker at
3,820.13 after Bundesbank chief Hans Tietmeyer helped to fuel rate
hike speculation.
</P>
<P>
Tietmeyer hinted at an increase following stronger-than-
expected wholesale prices data.
</P>
<P>
However, in post-bourse electronic trading the IBIS DAX index
rose in line with Wall Street and was also helped by the dollar's
recovery. The index closed 72.92 points higher at 3,869.53.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse also ended sharply higher, with the CAC-40
index up 64.55 points at 2,898.62, after the Bank of France said
it was leaving its key intervention rate unchanged at 3.1 percent.
</P>
