<HEADLINE> Britain to Cancel 132m-Pound Commonwealth Debts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The British government
announced today that it will cancel up to 132 million pounds
(about 212 million U.S. dollars) in debts owed by some poor
Commonwealth countries.
</P>
<P>
Britain's International Development Secretary Clare Short said
in a statement issued here today that she hoped Britain's move
would encourage other donor countries to consider new initiatives
to ease the burden of the world's poorest nations.
</P>
<P>
"Developing countries who are committed to poverty elimination
are in part hampered by their debt burden. We want to support
these countries in their efforts to improve the lives of poor
people," she said in the statement.
</P>
<P>
However, Short stressed that this program would depend on the
country "pursuing good government, encouraging transparency, and
applying economic policies which benefit the poor and encourage
sustainable economic development."
</P>
<P>
Countries including most Caribbean nations and African states
are likely to benefit from the new drive. 
</P>
