<HEADLINE> France Backs Mediation by Arab League in Comoros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- France today expressed its
support to the forthcoming mediation by the Arab League in the
Indian Ocean island nation of Comoros, which is in the midst of a
crisis between the central government and two separatist islands
of Anjouan and Moheli.
</P>
<P>
The French Minister of Cooperation Charles Josselin said that
France keeps a "diplomatic posture" in the on-going conflict in
the Comoros, and does not want to get involved in the
"institutional debate" of the Comoros.
</P>
<P>
"There is a fact, which is the Islamic Federal Republic of the
Comoros and it is up to all the Comorans to find a solution,"
said Josselin at a press conference on French aid to Comoros.
</P>
<P>
An envoy of the Arab League, Mohammad al-Khazindar, will begin
his mediation for the Comoros on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He will first pay a visit to the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) to seek a coordinated position with it in looking for a
political solution to the crisis, said an Arab League spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"The mediation of the OAU has marked the steps, and a new
mission will be conducted by the Arab League. We cannot but
support it,"said Josselin.
</P>
<P>
He said that France will provide an aid to Anjouan and Moheli,
but France alone cannot help the whole archipelago realize what he
called "an ambitious plan of development."
</P>
<P>
"France is ready to participate, with other financial backers,
in particular Europeans, in such a plan of development, without
that such and such part of the archipelago have the impression of
being forgotten," he said.
</P>
<P>
Josselin also said that France is maintaining contact with both
President Abdoulkarim Taki and the separatist government of
"Political-Administrative Coordination of Anjouan."
</P>
<P>
Anjouan and Moheli declared "independence" in early August. A
government military intervention in Anjouan last month resulted in
a fiasco. 
</P>
