parties to uphold their commitments to peace and to desist from
the "divide-and-rule" tactics.
</P>
<P>
Peace is a necessary ingredient in the development of the
country which all organizations, groups, political leaders and
citizens should actively promote and nurture, said Chibesa.
</P>
<P>
She challenged the Zambian women to be in the fore front of
talking and practizing peace.
</P>
<P>
"In this role, you are instruments for peace and have a duty
to influence your husbands toward positive thinkings," she said.
</P>
<P>
Chibesa also appealed to youths to be responsible citizens and
cautioned them against being manipulated and used as
"instruments" of destruction in the country by "selfish"
politicians. 
