<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Swiss Federal Council
(government) said today that the suspension of a Swiss special
fund caused by the absence of three Jewish members was a
"deplorable" incident.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Swiss government praised members from the
World Jewish Restitution Organization and asked them to have their
suggestions ready by December 25 to resume the work of the special
fund for holocaust victims and their families.
</P>
<P>
Four days ago, three Jewish members announced that they would
not attend the second meeting of the fund's seven-member direction
today. At least six direction members should be present when any
decision is made, according to its rules. The fund's work was
brought to a halt by the absence.
</P>
<P>
At its first meeting last July, the direction decided to raise
17 million Swiss francs (about 11 million US dollars) for the
fund. 
