<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improves Democracy, Legal System (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On how to ensure government functionaries to handle
administrative affairs in accordance with the law, Gu Angran,
director of the Commission of Legislative Affairs under the
National Preple's Congress Standing Committee, said that they must
act in accordance with the law in exercising the administrative
power.
</P>
<P>
The legalization of administrative management requires a
complete set of laws in this respect, a unified procedural law and
a system to supervise law enforcement. At present, some laws have
been formulated and others are still on the drawing board, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Administrative institutions and their functionaries are subject
to the supervision of judicial departments as well as their
self-supervision. The administrative procedural law has been
adopted for this purpose, he said.
</P>
<P>
All citizens, legal persons and organizations have the right to
acquire compensations if they suffer losses as a result of
administrative acts which violate laws. Hence, the state has
promulgated the compensation law, he added.
</P>
<P>
These laws have ensured that the administrative institutions
and their functionaries observe laws and perform their public
duties according to law.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the progress in the work of legal aid, Xiao Yang
said the system of legal aid is an important part of China's
judicial system and a major step to improving the social security
system so as to guarantee the rights and interests of the poor,
the weak and the disabled.
</P>
<P>
It has played a big role in promoting economic and social
reforms, practicing judicature fairly, easing social
contradictions and maintaining social stability, Xiao added.
</P>
<P>
Since the system was built in 1994, over 60 legal aid organs
have been set up at various levels, handling more than 5,000
cases, he added.
</P>
<P>
On working out laws on the market economy, Gu Angran said the
establishment of the socialist market economy must be protected by
a full-fledged legal system.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the NPC and its Standing Committee has adopted
a series of laws to standardize market operation and market order,
strengthen macro-economic control and improve social security, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Under the NPC legislation plans, China will formulate laws on
contracts, property rights, management of state assets,
securities, trust, anti-monopoly and pricing, some of which have
been submitted to the NPC Standing Committee for examination and
approval, Gu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
