<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doping Cases Increase by 80 percent in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Britain found 90 athletes to
be tested positive for banned drugs over the past year, with an
alarming 80 percent increase in findings for use of anabolic
steroids, according to the U.K. Sports Council Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The council's annual anti-doping study reported that 98 percent
of athletes tested negative in 4,469 controls carried out in
1996-97.
</P>
<P>
Of the 90 positive findings, the majority were for stimulants
(40) and anabolic agents (27).
</P>
<P>
Officials expressed concern over the large increase in steroid
cases, compared to 15 the previous year.
</P>
<P>
"This represents the largest number of findings ever for
anabolic agents over a one-year period in the U.K. testing
program," said Michele Verroken, director of the council's
anti-doping division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning To Step Up Reform of State Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The key to get Liaoning
Province's state firms out of debt in three years is to implement
the guidelines set in Jiang Zemin's report to the Party Congress
on reform of state firms, the governor of the province, Wen
Shizhen said here today.
</P>
<P>
As a major traditional base, Liaoning is home to 1400 large
state-owned enterprises, or one third of China's total. These
enterprises boast 360 billion yuan in fixed assets, said Wen, who
is attending the five-yearly Party congress which opened on
September 12.
</P>
<P>
With Chinese economy shifting from a planned economy to a
socialist market economy, some 50-60 percent of the enterprises
were making losses, though things have taken a turn for the better
in the recent few years as a result of bold experiments.
</P>
<P>
There still exist a lot of difficulties as well as potentials
and hopes in bringing state-owned enterprises out of debt, said
Wen.
</P>
<P>
By now, the province has worked out ways of managing state
firms well and all state firms are working hard to get themselves
out of debt. He said the on-going Party congress has charted a
right track for the future development of the state sector.
</P>
<P>
To realize the above target, the province has adopted effective
measures to take diversified forms of public ownership. Efforts
are being made to manage well large state firms while adopting a
flexible policy toward small ones and to invigorate state firms by
ways of merger, reorganization and readjustment.
</P>
<P>
According to the governor, the province has decided to
establish by the end of the century ten enterprise groups each
with an annual sales volume of 10 billion yuan, 20 groups each
with 5-9.9 billion yuan and 30 enterprise groups each with 2-4.9
billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Kidnapping Suspects Killed in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Two kidnapping suspects were
killed and three others wounded today in a Manila suburb by police
who successfully rescued a Chinese-Filipino businessman from the
hands of his abductors.
</P>
<P>
Police said a total of six gangmen were arrested during the
daring operation conducted in Laguna, 60 kilometers east of
Manila, early this morning.
</P>
<P>
They said Ruiz Saez-Co, 30, was rescued after being held for
eight days by the suspects who initially asked for 40 million
pesos (13 million U.S. dollars) in ransom.
</P>
<P>
Kidnap-for-ransom syndicates, mainly targeting rich
Chinese-Filipino businessmen, have been running rampant in the
archipelago country for years.
</P>
<P>
According to police statistics, there were 59 abductions
involving 94 victims during the first nine months of this year, a
sharp rise from the 23 cases recorded in the whole of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Both the government and its law enforcement agencies have been
sharply criticized for its failure to curb kidnappings, which have
already taken a toll on the economy by scaring away potential
investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Young Theorist On Deng Xiaoping Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A young theorist attending
the on-going 15th National Party Congress said the decision of
establishing Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology of the
Party will exert a great impact on China's future development.
</P>
<P>
"The banner is often deemed in China as an inspiring ideology,"
Li Zhongjie, a professor at the Party School of the CPC Central
Committee, said at a news conference Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee proposes that the Party, at its 15th
Congress, establish Deng Xiaoping Theory as its guilding
ideology by writing it into its Constitution is of "far-reaching
significance," he said.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that the CPC Central Committee decided to put Deng
Xiaoping theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
as the Party's guiding ideology and arm the whole Party with it at
the 14th National Party Congress in 1992. This theory of Deng's
was enriched at the current congress, he added.
</P>
<P>
On the question of the primary stage of socialism, Li said that
during this period, people, cherished great enthusiasm and grand
ideal, used to set a fairly high goal.
</P>
<P>
"They often neglect the actual conditions and difficulties
ahead and think that it will soon enter the higher stage of
socialism, committing a mistake of overleaping the phase of social
development," he added.
</P>
<P>
"However, haste makes waste," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The second and third generations of the central leadership
stated, after twists and turns stated at the 13th National Party
Congress in 1987 that China is still in the primary stage of
socialism, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The aim of stressing this, he said, is to firmly grasp the
basic contradictions in this stage and adhere to taking the
economic construction as the central task. All Party policies
should be based on this, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gloomy Commodities Trigger Australian Market Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed lower today as major investors re-evaluated the outlook for
resource companies based on a gloomy outlook for commodities
prices.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries Index closed 11.1 points down at 2651.8 and
the All Resources Index down 14.1 points at 1326.8.
</P>
<P>
"There were weaker major resource stocks again and if it wasn't
for WMC, which recovered most of its losses later, that
diversified resource sector could have been down significantly,"
Henderson Charlton Jones broker Brett O'Donovan said.
</P>
<P>
Among the major resource stocks to fall today, market
bellwether BHP had more than 1.5 percent of its share value cut to
finish at 16.1 Australian dollars, down 16 cents, while Rio Tinto
dropped 25 cents to 20.1 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index fell almost 2 percent amid market speculation
that a European central bank would soon announce it had sold off
its gold resources.
</P>
<P>
The gold index closed 24.5 points lower at 1252.8.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials Index closed 8.8 points lower at 4339.1.
</P>
<P>
Banking sector stocks were mixed. NAB lost some of yesterday's
gains, closing down 31.3 cents, Westpac Bank gained 3 cents and
ANZ dropped 5 cents while Commonwealth Bank was up 5 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, national turnover totaled 319.75 million shares, worth
855.6 million Australian dollars (616.03 million U.S. dollars),
with falls outnumbering rises 654 to 499.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
