<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Becomes Fourth NCR ATM Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A joint venture between
US-based National Cash Register (NCR), the world's leading ATM
supplier, and the Beijing Wire Communications Plant, was
established today, with China becoming the fourth country to
produce NCR ATMs.
</P>
<P>
The NCR (Beijing) Financial Equipment Systems Co. Ltd., which
was established with an investment of 19 million US dollars, will
manufacture state-of-the-art NCR products such as self-service
terminals.
</P>
<P>
The venture's annual production during initial operations is
expected to hit 580 units, and will rise to over 5,000 units
annually by 2002. Plans also call for the company to export
products to various Asian countries and regions after the year
2002.
</P>
<P>
China has a rapidly expanding market which "offers one of the
best growth opportunities" for the banking solutions offered by
NCR, according to NCR Vice-President Per-Olof Loof.
</P>
<P>
NCR holds a 70 percent share of the new venture, with the
remainder held by Beijing Wire.
</P>
<P>
NCR currently occupies 24 percent of the international
market. NCR also operates foreign production facilities in
Scotland, Canada and Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Delegates From Rural Areas Praise Jiang's Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A female delegate from
Fengyang County, where China's rural economic reform was
initiated, said here today that Jiang Zemin's call of holding high
the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory has given her assurance
of and encouragement for further economic reform.
</P>
<P>
In 1978, farmers in Fengyang County in east China's Anhui
Province cast away the form of People's Commune, a nationwide
form of production for decades, and experimented with the
household contract responsibility system with remuneration linked
to output. before long, this method was spread in rural areas
across China.
</P>
<P>
"In the years of practicing People's Commune, all villagers,
each of whom had an annual average income of not more than 100
yuan, lived in thatched huts. One third of the villagers went out
for begging," said the 41-year-old Wang Yinping, who is attending
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Fundamental changes have taken place in Fengyang County
during the 18-year reform and opening to the outside world, she
added.
</P>
<P>
To date, over 95 percent of farmers live in brick-and-tile
houses and some in multi-story buildings. The annual per capita
income of farmers in Fengyang rose to 1,800 yuan last year. All
school-age children have been admitted into school, said Wang,
who is secretary of the Xiquan Village Party Branch in Fengyang.
</P>
<P>
Twelve years ago when she was elected Party secretary,
the annual income of local farmers averaged 200 yuan. After
taking up her post, she led farmers to build a dozen of rural
factories and raised farmers' income to more than 3,000 yuan,
turning a poor village into a prosperous one, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin stressed in his report to the current Party
Congress that the Party will continue to stick to its fundamental
policies in rural areas, deepen rural reforms and increase
farmers' income by promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
"This has made us farmers be at ease. We will further
emancipate the mind, optimize agricultural structure, develop
rural industry and promote the industrial management of
agriculture so as to contribute our bit to putting an end to the
backwardness of rural areas," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Satisfied with Russian-Ukrainian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin today held talks with visiting Ukrainian Prime Minister
Valery Pustovoitenko, expressing his satisfaction with the current
bilateral relations, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that after his visit to Ukraine last May and the
signing of the Russian-Ukrainian agreement, the relations between
the two countries had raised to "a qualitatively different level."
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin expressed confidence that the Ukrainian Premier will
pursue "a policy of strong cooperation between Russia and Ukraine,
as it used to be for many centuries."
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko, who was appointed to the post in July 1997,
arrived here today for his first working visit to Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko is expected to hold talks with his Russian
counterpart Viktor Chernomyrdin and other senior officials in
order to tackle some unresolved problems, such as issues of
bilateral trade, the Black Sea Fleet, and the delimitation
of the borders. 
</P>
