<HEADLINE> Basuki Wins Princess Cup Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Yayuk Basuki of Indonesia
defeated Sarah Pitkowshi of France in a first-round victory in the
Princess Cup women's tennis tournament on Tuesday before rain
wiped out half the opening-day matches.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Basuki, the world number 22 and Tuesday's
highest-ranked player, outlasted Pitkowski 7-5 7-6 (7-3).
</P>
