<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Joseph Yam Named Central Banker of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Joseph Yam, chief executive
of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA), has been named the
Central Banker of the Year by the Euromoney magazine, the HKMA
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Each year, Euromoney's editors select from among the world's
central bankers the best central banker of the year and announce
the result in its September issue at the time of the World
Bank/International Monetary Fund annual meetings.
</P>
<P>
The magazine said, Yam has "successfully steered Hong Kong
through what was billed as the most tumultuous year in its
history," referring to the handover in the mid-year and the recent
regional currency turmoil.
</P>
<P>
"He has striven to build Hong Kong's domestic debt market
through the introduction of a government yield-curve, has built
the Exchange Fund, and has introduced Asia's most sophisticated
interbank real-time gross settlement system. His latest project
is to create a mortgage corporation along the lines of Fannie Mae
in the U.S.," said Euromoney.
</P>
<P>
"I am very honored to have been offered this award by
Euromoney," said Yam. "The credit is due not to me but to all my
dedicated colleagues at the HKMA."
</P>
<P>
An award presentation ceremony will be held here on September
22.
</P>
<P>
Yam started his civil service career in Hong Kong as a
statistician in 1971 and was appointed to the current post in
1993.
</P>
<P>
He was involved in the creation of Hong Kong's linked exchange
rate system in 1983 and is responsible for many of the reform
measures introduced since then to strengthen Hong Kong's monetary
system and develop Hong Kong's debt market. These measures have
contributed to monetary stability in Hong Kong and its development
as an international financial center, according to the HKMA, the
de facto central bank in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Yam was named the Best Asian Central Banker in 1996 by
Euromoney and in 1995 he was given the Banker of the Year Award by
the Hong Kong Institute of Bankers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
