<HEADLINE> PNA Urges US to Pressure Israel on Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) today sent an urgent message to the United States,
asking it to pressure Israel to eradicate Jewish settlements from
East Jerusalem's Ras Al-Amud.
</P>
<P>
PNA chief peace negotiator Saeb Erekat told the Palestinian
Legislative Council in Ramallah today that the situation in Ras
Al-Amud is worrying and the PNA has sent an urgent message to the
United State for help.
</P>
<P>
Three Jewish families moved into two empty houses in Ras
Al-Amud Sunday night, causing uproar among the nearby Palestinians
who threatened to kick them out if they do not leave by themselves.
</P>
<P>
A tense situation is prevailing in East Jerusalem because the
Jewish settlers till now are reluctant to move out. More Israeli
border policemen were called in to maintain order there.
</P>
<P>
Erekat said PNA officials from Jerusalem plans to hold an
urgent meeting Thursday to decide what steps would be taken if the
settlers do not move out from the area.
</P>
<P>
The local Palestinians will hold protest meetings if this issue
can not be solved timely, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli police officers have warned that clashes and
confrontations could erupt between Palestinians and Israelis not
only in East Jerusalem, but also in other PNA territories if
this issue drags on and political situation further
deteriorates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
