<HEADLINE> Syria Calls for New US Policy of Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Syrian official newspapers
today called on the United States to adopt a new policy to support
the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Syrian newspapers Teshreen and Al-Thawara made the call
following the U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright's first
visit to the region since taking office early this year.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. should assess the outcome of Albright's visit, what
she has heard and seen, and the hardline stance of Israel toward
the peace process, the Teshreen newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Such an assessment is supposed to lead to a new U.S. policy
supporting those who want peace and rebuking those who obstruct it
at a critical stage of the peace process deadlocked by the
practices of Israel, it added.
</P>
<P>
The paper affirmed what Syria had made it clear to Albright
that it adheres to the Mideast peacemaking and is ready to
establish a fair and overall peace based on the resolutions of the
United Nations Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The Al-Thawara newspaper expressed the hope that Albright's
first Mideast tour would mark a new stage in which the U.S. is to
play a fairer role in persuading Israel to take the right course
toward achieving peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
The paper maintained that it is the U.S. that can exert
pressures effectively on Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
to refrain from persisting in his hardline positions that portend
the most disastrous consequences to the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
