<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Technology Benefiting Northwest China Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Imported technology has helped
agricultural development on the infertile and dry land of China's
Loess Plateau.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Province is one of the beneficiaries. For the past five
years, it has imported agricultural technology from abroad and has
sent 3,800 people to be trained in foreign countries, bringing
direct economic returns worth around 500 million yuan (60 million
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The province is especially interested in technology for crop
breeding, seed selection, increasing output, and dry land grain,
oil-bearing crops, cotton, and apple production, local agronomists
say.
</P>
<P>
It has bought some 50 types of high-quality apple to increase
the competitiveness of Shaanxi's apples on the domestic and
international markets.
</P>
<P>
Jingyang Township has built a vegetable-growing base by using
imported covering materials and greenhouse technology. The
vegetable farm sells over 500,000 yuan of vegetable daily.
</P>
</TEXT>
