<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Makes Progress Protecting the Ozone Layer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- China has scored remarkable
achievements in protecting the ozone layer over the past 10 years
by eliminating over 20,000 tons of ozone depleting substances
(ODS).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at today's press conference marking the Third
International Ozone Layer Protection Day, leading officials from
the National Environmental Protection Agency (Nepa) said that
China's work to protect the ozone layer have been greatly
strengthened since the establishment of the national leading group
on ozone layer protection in 1992. The leading group is comprised
of officials from 18 ministries, including Nepa.
</P>
<P>
The leading group drafted the National Program for Phasing Out
Ozone Depleting Substances In China and wide-ranging related
strategies for eight sectors, including the chemical and household
refrigerator manufacturing industries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China has adopted measures to control the
protection and use of ODS and encourage enterprises to use ODS
substitutes.
</P>
<P>
China signed the "Vienna Convention for the Protection of
the Ozone Layer" and the "London Amendment of the Montreal
Protocol on Substances Which Deplete the Ozone Layer" in 1989 and
1991, and has since received a 150 million US dollars foreign
grant to phase out ODS.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
