<HEADLINE> UN Agency And New Silk Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The UN Development Program
(UNDP) will help promote trade and opening up along the new Silk
Road, according to Arthur N. Holcombe, UNDP representative to
China.
</P>
<P>
Holcombe made the remark at a recent forum here on economic and
trade co-operation between China and five Central Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
The second Eurasian Continental Railway, which runs more than
10,000 km from China to Europe, and which is known as the new Silk
Road, was opened to traffic in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP will arrange regional projects in the next five to ten
years to solve trade problems between China and the Central Asian
countries, such as lowering transport costs on the railway and
shortening the time for transported goods to cross borders.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP plans to provide technical aid for developing frontier
trade, industrial investment, poverty relief, and environmental
protection. The organization will send experts in mid-October to
do preparatory work for projects, Holcombe said.
</P>
<P>
Countries along the line have great potential for
co-operation. At Horgas, on the Chinese side, business people from
Zhejiang province in the east do 120 million US dollars worth of
business annually.  
</P>
