<HEADLINE> Multimedia Asia '97 Conference Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Multimedia Asia '97
Conference and Exhibition opened here today with a call for the
setting up of a virtual forum -- the Virtual commonwealth of
Nations -- to formulate a new global framework for information age
governance and towards nurturing a global civil society.
</P>
<P>
The call was made today by Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad when he opened the four-day conference-cum-exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the widening gap between the information poor and
the information rich society pointed to the need for a new
framework of governance where the concerns of distributive justice
existed alongside a free market system for the digital economy.
</P>
<P>
"The information age, the new basis for power, wealth and
influence, will be knowledged. No one has the monopoly of
knowledge and wisdom, meaning no one can have all the power,
wealth and influence," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the virtual commonwealth of nations, multimedia
technology such as videophony and teleconferencing could be used
as a means to communicate and discuss issues of concern and
problems with each other.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC), as
Malaysia's investment for the future, using the concept of smart
partnership, was an invitation for the world community to together
shape a common future.
</P>
<P>
"We invite collaboration instead of confrontation, enrichment
instead of exploitation, sharing instead of grabbing. These should
remain the watchwords, these should provide the basis towards
evolving a just and equitable global society," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Multimedia Asia '97 with the theme "Moving MSC From Vision
to Reality; Benchmarking Smart Solution " is an annual gathering
of experts and investors to discuss on the MSC programs.
</P>
<P>
The Multimedia Asia 97 Conference and Exhibition attracted some
600 delegates and participants.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's MSC is a designated 15 kilometers by 50 kilometers
multimedia hub encompassing the Kuala Lumpur City Center, the
Kuala Lumpur International Airport in Sepang and the new
administrative capital in Putrajaya.  
</P>
</TEXT>
