<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
declined on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost another 11.5 points to close at 1,920.6
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 130.94 million units, worth
279.64 million Singapore dollars (about 185.19 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 274 to 78, while 258
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Rekapac was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 6.41 million units. It was followed by ABR Holdings
which had 6.29 million shares traded. MBf Capital was next with
4.85 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Technology Auto led the gainers of the day as it
rose by 24 cents to finish at 4.72 Singapore dollars. Asean Fund,
JMH 400, Singapore Technology Aero, and the Thai Prime Fund
increased by 20 cents each to close at 12 US dollars, 8.15 US
dollars, 4.24 Singapore dollars, and 6.7 US dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, NBT was the biggest loser as it declined by
four dollars to end at 14 Singapore dollars. The Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell by 80 cents to close at 23.1 Singapore
dollars, while Creative 50 finished 70 cents lower at 33.1
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
