<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unrest Hits Ujungngpandang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Violence erupted since Monday
evening in Ujungpandang, capital city of Indonesia's South
Sulawesi province, has destroyed more than 100 shops along the
main streets in the city, according to reports reaching here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the city has not return to normal till noon
today, despite security measures have been taken by the local
authorities, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The violence broke out at 20:00 on Monday when a 9 year-old
girl was killed by a 28 year-old man who was believed to be a
mental patient.
</P>
<P>
The incident triggered many residents attacking on the mental
patient and his home and then spread to a broad violence in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The people who involved in the unrest torched shops and
vehicles along the streets of Somba Opu, Sulawesi, Ratulangi,
Cenderawasih, Bulusaraung, Bawakaraeng, destroying hundreds of
shops and dozens of vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Troops and policemen have been deployed on main streets in the
city, but the situation has not been completely returned to normal
as many shops and schools being closed till noon today, added the
reports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
