<HEADLINE> Uganda to Hold Domestic Tourism Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 16 (Xinhua)--Uganda Tourist Board has
decided to hold the first ever domestic tourism exhibition here
in the last week of this month, reported the local daily, The New
Vision today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will coincide with the world tourism day, which
falls on September 27.
</P>
<P>
The board has invited several tour agents, operators,
hoteliers and companies offering tourism related services to take
part in the exhibition, the paper said, adding that over 5,000
exhibition visitors are expected here in Kampala.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the exhibition is to provide an ideal forum for
facilitating interaction and opportunity to appreciate the beauty
endowed to Uganda in terms of flora and fauna, a release issued
by the board last week was quoted as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
