<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Powerful Typhoon Hits Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A powerful typhoon struck
Kagoshima Prefecture, southwestern Japan, this morning, triggering
a landslide which left one dead, three injured and two missing,
local authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon, the season's 19th, hit Makurazaki in Kagoshima
Prefecture on Japan's southernmost main island of Kyushu shortly
after 8 a.m., the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
In the town of Tashiro, six people went missing after a
landslide buried three houses. Of the four who escaped or were
rescued, one later died, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
Some 340 houses in the prefecture were flooded, while 64,000
homes in the prefecture and its neighboring Miyazaki prefecutre
suffered power cuts.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon, accompanied by strong winds and heavy showers,
halted major road and air traffic in the Kyushu region.
</P>
<P>
Japan's three airlines said 110 domestic flights to and from
the Kyushu region and surrounding areas were canceled.
</P>
<P>
Ferries and ships to and from the region were also cancelled.
</P>
</TEXT>
