<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Congress as Seen by Ordinary Chinese (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Huang, who is from the city of Changde in central-south China's
Hunan province, saw during the summer vacation that people back
home were trying to deal with the difficulties they faced. "It's
good that Comrade Jiang has clarified the ambiguities in the
share-holding system in his report," she said, noting that her
worker parents could understand the system better and relax a
little bit.
</P>
<P>
Jiao Qi, also at Qinghua, still remembers the slogan calling
for young people to devote themselves to the country's
prosperity. It become popular among Qinghua students in the spring
of 1979 when China had just launched its reform and opening-up
drive. Although it's old, it's not out of date, she said.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping opened up the path for building socialism with
Chinese characteristics. Jiang Zemin made clear that China would
hold the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory high, and under
these circumstances, Jiao believes that revitalizing China will
work if everyone takes part.
</P>
<P>
Wenzhou, in east China, is known as the cradle of business
talent. Where there's a market, there are people from Wenzhou;
Where there is no market, people from Wenzhou will make one. The
city's seven million urban and rural residents have over 45
billion yuan (5.4 billion U.S. dollars) deposited in the
bank. Foreign currency deposits amount to 300 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Li Yuesheng, director of a switch plant in Wenzhou, said
that he found both markets and opportunities for his factory in
Jiang's speech.
</P>
<P>
"The economic system reform, which will continue after the
Congress, will promote economic growth," Li said, adding, "Jiang
said that the ownership structure will be adjusted and perfected,
and this will be a very good chance for us."
</P>
<P>
As a private entrepreneur, Li is not afraid to extend his
business. What he worries most about is whether the country's
policy will be changed or not.
</P>
<P>
"Once the status and role of the private businesses are
recognized, we'll make an all-out effort to transform the city's
power network and bring benefits to society," Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
