<HEADLINE> Japan Beats South Korea in Asian Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Japan recorded a surprising
win over South Korea 89-83 at the Asian Men's Basketball
Championship in Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
Maikeru Takahashi scored 31 points for the Japanese squad,
added by towering 2.16 meter center Akifumi Yamasaki with 16 as
Japan shocked its old rival in a late match on Monday.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, tipped to meet favourite China in the final, will
have to beat in-form Chinese Taipei and Iran in their remaining
group B matches to enter the last four.
</P>
<P>
Huang Chun-hsiung top scored for Chinese Taipei as the squad
kept its impressive run going with a 72-54 win over Iran.
</P>
<P>
China, bidding for a sixth consecutive title, used its star
performers time and again to beat Jordan 95-62 in group A. Wang
Zhizhi, Asia's top player, scored 14 points in 17 minutes of
action.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Saudi Arabia scored a win of 90-76 over United Arab
Emirates. 
