<HEADLINE> Zambia Urges Diplomats to Attract Foreign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 16 (xinhua) -- zambia has urged its
diplomats abroad to attract foreign investors who will come and
expand the production base in Zambia, a financial weekly paper
published here reported today.
</P>
<P>
Briefing a team of Zambian diplomats who have been accredited
to various countries as trade commissioners, Mwansa Musonda,
Executive Director of the Export Board of Zambia, called on the
diplomats to source more foreign investors who will invest
heavily in export production in the country so that enough stocks
can be produced for the export market.
</P>
<P>
"Please help us source more production oriented investors who
will come and increase our exports so that we can meet the rising
demand in foreign markets," said Musonda.
</P>
<P>
He intimated that there are ready markets for almost all
products exported from Zambia although the volumes needed to be
increased according to demand.
</P>
<P>
Musonda singled out the agricultural sector which he said has
enormous potential for expansion since the country has vast
arable land and easily accessible water for commercial
production.
</P>
<P>
The agro-processing sub-sector is another area with immense
potential for increased earnings because of the value added to
the end product, Musonda said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the diplomats will work tirelessly in their
countries of accreditation to woo more foreign direct investors
into Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
