<HEADLINE> Strong Players to Compete in China Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The 328,000 U.S. dollars ATP
Tour China Open will take place at the Beijing International
Tennis Center from September 29 to October 5, sanctioned by the
Chinese Tennis Association (CTA) and State Sports Commission.
</P>
<P>
Former world no.1 player Jim Courier and former Grand Slam Cup
Champion, David Wheaton of the United States will play in the
tournament as wild card players.
</P>
<P>
Courier, currently ranked 22nd in the world, said he had hoped
to play in China years ago and was delighted to now have the
opportunity of playing in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Contenders for the fiercely guarded champion title will include
last year Beijing Open finalist Martin Damm of the Czech Republic,
world top doubles player and Olympic Gold Medalist Mark Woodforde
of Australia, one half of the infamous "Woodies" pair and partner
of compatriot Todd Woodbridge. Both Damm anf Woodforde, currently
ranked 42nd and 46th, are hot favourites for the final.
</P>
<P>
The exceptionally strong player field also includes Thomas
Johansson of Sweden, ranked 33rd, his compatriots Tahitian Fabrice
Santoro and Magnus Gustafsson, Byron Black of Zimbabwe and winner
of the ATP Tour Shanghai Open earlier this year, Jan Kroslak of
Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Chinese top tennis player will get another wild card.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese fans will be disppointed to see world no. 2 Michael
Chang's absence in the tournament. 
</P>
