<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Expresses Desire in Joining APEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President
Chandrika Kumaratunga today expressed her country's interest in
joining the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC).
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga, who arrived here on Monday on a four-day visit,
voiced the desire during her meeting with Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad here today, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah
Ahmad Badawi said at a news briefing.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Badawi said that on this point, Mahathir told the Sri
Lankan president that there was no decision to expand the
membership (of APEC) at this time but when the time came Malaysia
would give its support to Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga told Mahathir that Sri Lanka would propose that
Malaysia be included in the Group of 24 (G24) since there was a
vacancy, Badawi said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the two leaders also touched on other
international issues including promoting closer ties between ASEAN
(the Association of Southeast Asian Nations), of which Malaysia is
a member, and the South Asia Association for Regional Cooperation
(SAARC), of which Sri Lanka is a member.
</P>
<P>
Badawi said that on human right issues, Mahathir explained
Malaysia's view and the Sri Lankan president agreed there was
ground to review the declaration on human rights made by the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
"This means that there is support from Sri Lanka in the
matter," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir also discussed with the Sri Lankan president the share
and financial market.
</P>
<P>
Badawi said that Mahathir explained how manipulation of
currency had caused hardships to developing countries.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral issues, both leaders agreed to enhance bilateral
ties, including expanding cooperation in the fields of economy,
investment, training and information technology.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has sought Malaysia's cooperation to train its
officers in line with its move to reform its Civil Service and
Malaysia was prepared to provide such training.  
</P>
