<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Delegates Stress Importance of Party Building (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- To advance the cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics in an all-round
way to the 21st century, it is essential to uphold, strengthen and
improve the leadership of the Party and do well in Party building.
</P>
<P>
This is the general view shared by the delegates to the
on-going 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
held in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Party building is one of the most heated topics at the congress
which opened here on September 12.
</P>
<P>
Now that the Party is leading the Chinese people in building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, the question of what kind
of Party it should be has vital bearing on the future of China,
delegates said.
</P>
<P>
"The report delivered by Jiang Zemin stressed the importance of
strengthening Party discipline," said Ismail Amat, state
councillor and minister in charge of the State Nationalities
affairs Commission, pointing out this is of major significance for
improving and strengthening Party leadership.
</P>
<P>
"The part concerning Party building in the report proves
forceful, and it has won the heart of all delegates," said Yang
Guoping, commander of China's Armed Police Force.
</P>
<P>
Centering on how to do a better job in Party building so as to
implement the task of the Party as defined in the report, the
delegates have offered many suggestions.
</P>
<P>
Chen Guangwen, deputy secretary of the Beijing Municipal Party
Committee, said special attention should be paid to the following
four aspects.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Delegates Stress Importance of Party Building (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
First, The building of the Party should be geared to the theory
and line of the Party.
</P>
<P>
Second, the building of the Party should be carried out through
carrying forward fine traditions and, more importantly,
emphasizing creating new experience.
</P>
<P>
Third, the relationships between the work in the areas of
ideology, organization and work style should be handled properly,
with emphasis on the ideological area.
</P>
<P>
Fourth, in training and selecting cadres, relevant principles
should be observed, ensuring that they are more revolutionary,
well-educated, younger and professionally more competent.
</P>
<P>
Tian Fengshan, governor of Heilongjiang Province, urged his
comrades to improve Party practices in four aspects as set forth
in Jiang Zemin's report to the congress.
</P>
<P>
He said it is necessary to make it a common practice within the
entire Party to study conscientiously, hold democratic discussions,
try to explore new ways and be realistic and pragmatic.
</P>
<P>
The deputy head of the Organization Department of the CPC
Central Committee, Zhang Quanjing, gave his opinions about
strengthening Party discipline which he described as a fine
tradition of the Party and a vital organizational guarantee for
the country to score more victories.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pointed out that strengthening Party discipline has
special significance in the light of the current situation within
the Party.
</P>
</TEXT>
