<HEADLINE> World's Largest Piece Of Jade Found in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A 1,000-ton block of jade
that was found in Xiuyan county in northeast China's Liaoning
Province is believed to be the largest piece in the world.
</P>
<P>
The variegated jade is estimated at 20 meters high and 10
meters wide, and is more than 740 tons heavier than the previous
record holder, which was also found in Xiuyan, known as the home
to jades.
</P>
<P>
Most of the huge piece of jade was buried in a hillside. The
county government has a plan for removing the "national
treasure". The work is expected to be completed by the end of this
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
