<HEADLINE> Reception Marks 25th Anniversary of China-Togo Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A reception was held here
today to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the establishment of
Sino-Togolese diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
The reception was hosted by the Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries and China-Africa Friendship
Association.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, President of the China-Africa
Friendship Association Gong Dafei said China and Togo have
conducted fruitful cooperation based on equality and mutual
benefit in politics, economy, trade, heath, culture and other
areas since they forged diplomatic ties in September 1972.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have always supported each other and treated
each other equally, Gong said.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of sister-city relations between Lome and
South China's Shenzhen in 1996 widened the areas of cooperation
between the two countries, Gong added.
</P>
<P>
Togo's Ambassador to China Nolana Ta Ama said the leaders and
peoples of Togo and China have maintained profound friendship over
the past 25 years.
</P>
<P>
The ever-increasing and multi-form cooperation between the two
countries has benefited the Togolese people, he said.
</P>
<P>
China has helped Togo to attain the goal of self-sufficiency in
grain supply and offered assistance to Togo in medical care,
sports and other aspects, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he noted, Togo has supported and will continue to
back China's great cause of reunification.
</P>
<P>
Both Gong and Ta Ama expressed the hope that China and Togo
will continue to support each other in the future and achieve
common development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
