<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Media Seminar in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Journalists
Association and the Japan Newspaper Publishers and Editors
Association today sponsored a seminar in Beijing on "The
Responsibility and Role of the Chinese and Japanese Media Workers
in the 21st Century".
</P>
<P>
It was held to commemorate the 25th anniversary of the
normalization of diplomatic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 30 senior journalists attended the seminar and discussed
the history of the Sino-Japanese friendship.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the importance of China-Japan relations in
the new post-Cold War world, how to develop good-neighborly
friendship for the 21st century, the development of bilateral
relations, and the role of journalists of the countries in all
this.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that it is their duty to report on exchanges
between the two governments and the two peoples in an objective
and friendly way, to cover bilateral co-operation in politics, the
economy and culture, and to demonstrate the two peoples' desire
for friendship.
</P>
<P>
They said that the two countries' journalists should make a
concerted effort to promote China-Japan friendship for the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Shao Huaze and Zheng Mengxiong, the president and vice-president
of the All-China Journalists Association, respectively, met with
the Japanese guests at the seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
