<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enterprise Reform To Be Expedited (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The on-going 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China has made a theoretical
breakthrough in the nature and role of shareholding system, which
is to accelerate the reform of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from the industrial circles shared the view: the
Congress has gone beyond the scope that the public sector of the
economy not only comprises the state- and collectively-owned
sectors, but also the state- and collectively-owned elements in
the sector of mixed ownership. It is a form of capital
organization of modern enterprises, which is favorable for
separating ownership from management and raising the efficiency of
the operation of enterprises and capital.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Ruimin, general manager of the Haier Group in Qingdao,
Shandong Province, said the theory on public ownership in Jiang
Zemin's report made at the opening session of the 15th Party
Congress will help to broaden our vision on China's enterprise
reform, serving as a strategic program document guiding the reform of
state-owned firms.
</P>
<P>
After the conclusion of the 15th party Congress, the process in
which large- and medium-sized state-owned enterprises will be
turned into corporations will be accelerated, said another
delegate.
</P>
<P>
Liu Haiyan, a manager of Beijing-based Yanshan Petro-chemical
Corporation, said the global competition of national strength is
mainly reflected among large enterprises and enterprise groups.
The introduction of the shareholding system will help to enhance
the strength of state-owned firms by raising funds through forming
enterprise groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
