<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province to Hold Commodity Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
province, a major heavy industrial base in the country, will hold
a commodity fair in the port city of Dalian from September 18 to
20.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the fair will have more than 600
booths. It will be sponsored by eight departments of the
provincial and the Dalian city governments.
</P>
