<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 07:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran to Launch Military Maneuver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Iran is to launch its most
extensive military maneuver involving 200,000 troops during the
Defense Week starting from next Monday, local newspapers reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Ali Shahbazi, chief of the joint
staff of the army, at a press conference with domestic reporters
Monday, and carried by four English dailies.
</P>
<P>
He said naval, ground and air forces would participate in the
maneuver, code-named "Zolfaqar," which will be carried out in the
Kooshk-e Nosrat region in Qom province, 156 kilometers south of
Iran's capital Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver is aimed at improving the fighting capabilities of
the armed forces, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the war game, which is Iran's most extensive one so
far, has different phases ranging from defense against chemical
attacks to electronic warfare under the supervision by 200
military experts.
</P>
<P>
Iranian-made planes as Dorna, Parastoo and O'oj as well as
Zolfaqar tanks will be tested during the maneuver and live
ammunition will be used throughout the operations, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
