<HEADLINE> Improving Transportation Facilities In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The capital of southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has been building a
more complete transportation network to help the economically
less-developed region.
</P>
<P>
The city has opened 371 bus routes to major cities in
neighboring areas such as Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Zhanjiang, Wenshan,
Kunming, Fuzhou, and Haikou, as well as 57 cities and counties in
Guangxi. There are more than 120 routes running to other provinces.
</P>
<P>
Work has also been done on local waterways, making it possible
for vessels of 1,000 DWT to sail as far east as Guangdong, Hong
Kong, and Macao, and for ships of 500 DWT to navigate westward to
Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city has opened 20 domestic air routes to big
cities of Beijing, Guangzhou, Shenyang, Chengdu, Kunming,
Shenzhen, Shanghai, Tianjin, Chongqing, Wuhan and Zhengzhou. One
route links Nanning to Hong Kong, and another two link the city
with Hanoi and Bangkok. Expansion of the Nanning Airport is also
under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
