<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Spending More On Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua)-- The residents of Guangzhou,
the capital of South China's Guangdong province, have shown a
great deal of zeal for buying insurance and negotiable securities
in the past three years.
</P>
<P>
The City Government Statistics Bureau says that in the first
half of the year, local residents spent 109 yuan on average on
negotiable securities, up 77 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Urban families have seen an annual average growth of 46 percent
in earnings from investments in the past three years.
</P>
<P>
Per capita income from such investments stood at 319 yuan last
year, accounting for 3.2 percent of the yearly income of 9,905
yuan, much higher than the national average. 
</P>
