<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Recovers From Slumping Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in southwest China handled imports and exports totaling 1.3
billion US dollars in the first seven months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented a six percent rise from the same period
in 1996 and ended a 13-month slump in exports.
</P>
<P>
Substantial increases in exports contributed to the the
recovery, with the number of commodities recording exports of more
than 10 million US dollars each growing from 16 to 25.
</P>
<P>
The region, which has abundant resources, increased exports of
zinc, tin, and antimony by 35 million US dollars during the first
half of this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the region is home to an ever increasing number of
overseas-funded businesses and other enterprises with the
authority to handle exports. The former exported 186 million US
dollars worth-of goods in the first half of the year, up 24
percent. The latter's exports shot up by 30 percent to 87 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's border trade jumped by 28 percent to top 80 million
US dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
Major exports included meat, fruit, leather products, textiles,
jewelry, nonferrous metals, cement, pesticides and household
electrical appliances.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
