<HEADLINE> Malaysia, S.Lanka Sign Economic Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Sri Lanka
today signed three government-to-government agreements on
economic, scientific and technical Cooperation, the Avoidance of
Double Taxation and the Prevention of Fiscal Evasion with respect
to taxes on income.
</P>
<P>
The accords were signed following talks between Malaysian Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohamad and visiting Sri Lankan President
Chandrika Kumaratunga. Both were present at the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Both leaders also witnessed the signing of Four memorandums of
understanding (MOUs) between the Malaysian private sector and the
Board of Investment of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The MOUs are on the proposed development of an industrial
township, an industrial zone, a science park, Colombo's airport
expansion and the promotion of multimedia enterprise.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan president arrived here yesterday for a four-day
visit to Malaysia.  
</P>
