<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Advertising Industry Faces Negative Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's advertising
industry will most likely face its first year of negative growth
this year, according to industry sources.
</P>
<P>
The economic slowdown and the government's belt-tightening
policy have hit many companies hard, forcing them to slash costs,
including advertising budgets.
</P>
<P>
The industry has set a target of six percent growth for this
year, but the growth could be minus, the Nation newspaper
reported.
</P>
<P>
Last year's growth was on the back of rising media costs.
However, this year the severe macro-economic problems have caused
most media operators to lower their fees to attract buyers and
offer discount packages, such as "buy one, get one free."
</P>
<P>
This situation will certainly not bring about industry growth,
but only dampen expansion.
</P>
<P>
The negative growth view is shared by Rangsan Panpimanmas, an
associate media director of Prakit and FCB PLC.
</P>
<P>
Rangran said the present uncertainty makes it difficult to gain
a clear picture of the economic situation. There is no sign of
political stability and it is difficult to forecast the outcome
for the last quarter, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
