<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Re-talks About Canal Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's plan to build a
canal cross the Kra Isthmus, the narrowest point in southern
Thailand, is emerging again as the navy recently voiced its
support to it.
</P>
<P>
Thai navy commander Adm. Vijitr Chamnarnkarn Monday expressed
his support for Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh's idea to
revive the plan and build the canal in Ranong province to link the
Gulf of Thailand and the Andaman Sea.
</P>
<P>
The canal would provide a short-cut for shipping and help save
the state budget since Thai navy ships will no longer go round
Singapore when they want to travel from the Gulf of Thailand to
the Andaman Sea, Vijitr said.
</P>
<P>
The navy chief shrugged off fears that the canal would affect
national security, saying it would not generate problems like the
Suez and the Panama canals.
</P>
<P>
The canal would instead facilitate Thailand to deploy its
forces to protect its territorial waters, he was quoted as saying
by local newspapers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
