<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Month-Long Anti-Rat Drive Starts in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh on Monday kicked off
a month-long anti-rat campaign, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi State Minister for Information ABU Sayeed
inaugurated the rat elimination drive at a function organized by
the Agricultural Extension Directorate.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, the state minister described rats as
the "social and economic enemies" of the country, saying the
rodents destroy thousands of tons of grains every year, spread
diseases and damage daily usables and preserved items.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 1.4 million Bangladeshi farmers, students and people
from other strata killed some three million rats. As a result,
about 22,000 tons of rice were saved, according to local press
reports.
</P>
<P>
Widespread public awareness is the main pre-requisite for
making the rat elimination drive a success, Sayeed stressed.
</P>
<P>
The state minister urged scientists to find easy and cheap
rat-killing methods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
