<HEADLINE> India to Help Sri Lanka with Weather Forecast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- India will help Sri Lanka in
weather forecasting by providing data transmission equipment,
technical assistance and personnel training, the Daily News
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Meteorology of India will provide Sri Lanka
with a data transmission equipment, which can receive and process
data transferred from the Indian satellite INSAT, situated in a
geo-stationery orbit around 36,000 kilometers above the equator,
the report quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is around 80 million Sri Lankan
rupees (about 1.36 million U.S. dollars), of which 60 million
rupees (one million dollars) will come from India.
</P>
<P>
India will also provide all the technical assistance and
training, the report said.  
