<HEADLINE> Mir Main Computer Fixed up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Three cosmonauts on Russian
Mir space station this afternoon had fixed up the main computer
system, which had a new breakdown on Sunday's evening.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth breakdown of the cranky Mir computer this
year.
</P>
<P>
Cosmonauts used cells of three different models to replace
those of the main computer.
</P>
<P>
A new computer will be sent to the Mir space station in early
October this year.
</P>
<P>
The Mir station, which has been in orbit for 11 years, suffered
a string of breakdowns recently. But the cosmonauts were not in
any danger. 
</P>
