<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Electronics Industry Witnesses Speedy Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The introduction of high
technology has enabled the electronics industry in east China's
Zhejiang Province to grow at an annual growth rate of 42 percent
over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The industry, one of the leading local industries, generated
over 22 billion yuan in output value and 16 billion yuan in sales
in 1996, 5.73-fold and 6.27-fold increases on 1991 figures,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The industry exported products valued at over 4.3 billion yuan
in 1996, up 5.94-fold on 1991.
</P>
<P>
The notable achievements resulted from an extensive program to
introduce state-of-the-art technology.
</P>
<P>
The province has allocated over one billion yuan to 150 key
technological upgrading projects in the industry in recent years,
with the vast majority of new technology applied to production.
</P>
<P>
The province has emerged as one of the nation's major bases for
the production of more than 50 key electronics products, including
program-controlled telephone switchboards, mobile telephones,
computers, color monitors integrated circuits and television set.
</P>
<P>
Twenty local electronics enterprises are rated on the nation's
top 100 companies in the electronics industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
