<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, Philippines to Strengthen Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The visiting Philippine
President Fidel Ramos said here today that the Philippines hopes
to further strengthen bilateral ties with the Czech Republic on
politics, economy, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Ramos, who arrived here today for a three-day state visit to
Prague, made the remarks after meeting with his Czech counterpart,
Vaclav Havel.
</P>
<P>
Ramos pointed out that the potential for the two countries to
develop bilateral ties is great, and the trade volume between them
so far is not in keeping with their national status and power.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries will sign a new trade agreement and
other cooperative deals during his stay in the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Ramos will meet with Czech Prime Minister
Vaclav Klause, Chairman of the Chamber of Deputies Milos Zeman,
and Chairman of the Senate Peter Pithart on Tuesday to further
discuss deepening bilateral ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
