<HEADLINE> Latin American Fund to Support Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Latin
American-Panamanian Stock Exchange will help products from Panama
and Latin American nations enter international markets, an
official with the institution said today.
</P>
<P>
The stock exchange will favor the integration of production,
especially in agriculture and livestock to compete in the world
market, Latin American-Panamanian Stock Exchange marketing
coordinator Mileanne Martin told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Martin said the financial institution, the first of its kind to
be created in Latin America, will provide buyers and suppliers the
opportunity to bring their products to international markets from
Panama through financial agents. It also will help Panama and
other Latin American countries meet the World Trade Organization's
demands, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The stock market will help create and look for new markets for
regional producers.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the stock exchange will quicken trade
development in Panama which is one of the largest financial
centers on the continent, and it is also one step toward
integration, Martin stressed. 
</P>
