<HEADLINE> Shanghai's International Credit Card Connection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Anyone with a Visa card in
Shanghai, China's economic powerhouse, can now get Chinese
currency from 435 ATMs of the Industrial and commercial Bank of
China (ICBC).
</P>
<P>
This is the latest development in the city's financial
business, connecting its credit card network to the international
one.
</P>
<P>
Another commercial bank, the Bank of Communications, has
increased the number of ATM's that offer the same service to 50.
</P>
<P>
The ATM's started the Visa-Plus network in early June. In the
first two months of operation there were more than 860
withdrawals, valued at 1.23 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The RMB service is expected to be available at other commercial
banks' ATMs, and to link up with Mastercard.  
</P>
