<DOCNO> XIE19970916.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment in Netherlands Expected to Decline in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The number of unemployed
people in the Netherlands will drop to 400,000 in 1998 thanks to
improved economic performances, a Dutch government press list
reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobs in the country will have grown by 465,000
during the term of the present government, which ends in May next
year, says Dutch News Monitor, a selected list of government press
releases.
</P>
<P>
The number of full-time jobs fluctuates around the 3.7 million
mark, while the number of part-time jobs has grown to 1.8 million,
according to the news list.
</P>
<P>
There are also some 700,000 people in the Netherlands, mostly
young workers, who are content with temporary work.
</P>
<P>
However, the aging of the workforce and the growth in the
number of people over 65 -- from more than two million in 1996 to
an estimated four million in 2040 -- will stand out as a thorny
issue in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
