<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- Renato de Villa turned over the Department of National
Defense on Monday to Secretary Fortunato Abat in ceremonies at
Camp Aguinaldo in Quezon City. De Villa resigned in order to run
for the presidency next year.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star:
</P>
<P>
-- As he relinquished his post at the Department of National
Defense, outgoing Defense Secretary Renato de Villa asked on
Monday the military to stay away from partisan politics and defend
the constitution.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Initiative for Reform, Modernization and Action
Monday urged the supreme court to rule on its petition to allow
the Commission on Elections to verify the 7 million signatures it
had gathered in order that a peaceful plebiscite would be
conducted to determine the will of the people on charter changes.
</P>
<P>
The Business Daily:
</P>
<P>
-- The decidedly lackluster performance of the country's
economy this year has taken its toll on the confidence of
businessmen. More than a third of them expect a slowdown in the
national economy this year, a survey conducted by the Makati
Business Club said.  
</P>
