<HEADLINE> U.S. to Host Inaugural Ali Cup Amateur Boxing Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The city of Louisville
will play host to the inaugural Muhammad Ali Cup International
Amateur Boxing Challenge on Monday.
</P>
<P>
To highlight the tournament that bears his name, Ali smiled and
shook hands with representatives from the 21 nations that were to
compete in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The tournament, to be started on Monday night, is expected to
raise more than one million U.S. dollars for a planned Ali museum
and education center in Louisville and several USA Boxing youth
programs.
</P>
<P>
"We are proud to be here on this unique occasion, a boxing
competition in the name of the greatest of the great boxers the
world has ever produced," said Pakistan's Anwar Chowdhry,
president of the International Amateur Boxing Association. "It is
my wish and desire that this tournament should become an annual
feature."
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 boxers were to compete in the tournament, including
the top-ranked American boxers in 11 of 12 weight classes.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary bouts run through Wednesday, with the semifinals on
Thursday and the championship bouts on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
