<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guilin Rebuilds River Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Guilin, one of the best-known
scenic sites in China located in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, is currently rebuilding and expanding the Zhujiang Port to
offer services to foreign tourists.
</P>
<P>
Guilin is best known throughout the world for its picturesque
mountains and rivers.
</P>
<P>
The port, which has four berths and covers some 3,500 sq.m. has
the capacity to simultaneously anchor 60 boats and has a total
annual handling capacity of 450,000 passengers.
</P>
<P>
The expansion project will be carried out at a cost of 10
million yuan, with funding provided by the Guilin Wuzhou Tourism
Co. Ltd., owner of the port, and a Taiwan company.
</P>
<P>
The project will involve the refurbishing or expansion of a
number of facilities, including a luxury terminal, a service
system for the handicapped, a tourism information center and a
1,000 sq.m. parking lot, as well as restaurants and bars.
</P>
<P>
The new port will have an annual handling capacity of 1.5
million people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
