<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Carpet Export Slides Down in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's export of
carpet, one major export item of the country, decreased by 6.5
percent in August this year compared with the corresponding month
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the Carpet Manufacturers and
Exporters' Association, the total carpet export during the month
of August was to the tune of 11.62 million U.S. dollars whereas it
was 12.43 million dollars in August last year.
</P>
<P>
The decrease was termed by exporters as a result of withdrawal
of 47 percent rebate on the carpet exports by the government, said
the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Pakistan's carpet export declined by 51
percent in June and 36 percent in July this year compared with the
corresponding months in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, export of textile, another major export item of
Pakistan, also showed a decline of around 51 million dollars in
August compared with the same period in 1996, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
However, the export of ready-made garments went up 2.4 percent
and cotton bags up 17.74 percent while synthetic fabrics
registered an increase of 6.35 percent in the month of August 1997
compared with the corresponding month in 1996, according to the
sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
