<HEADLINE> Britain Pledges More Aid for Volcano-Hit Montserrat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Britain today pledged more aid
for Montserrat, stressing its commitment to the future of the
Caribbean island ravaged by volcano eruptions.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with the island's Chief Minister David Brandt,
Prime Minister Tony Blair agreed that Britain should build a new
airstrip for the island and provide a soft loan to enable its
government to avert a crisis for people buying their own homes.
</P>
<P>
Britain has so far announced a package of emergency aid worth
41.5 million pounds (66.5 million U.S. dollars), including a 6.5
million pound (10.4 million U.S. dollar) housing program. 
</P>
